  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nTG version: `master`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : c5162fc3e748303a10bb00bf29bb66e2df34490b\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n`eth_getBlockReceipts` returns the list of receipts for the provided block number.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nSometimes it returns the following error:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nnonce too high: address 0x274F3c32C90517975e29Dfc209a23f315c1e5Fc7, tx: 722226 state: 722223\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nThe issues is non-deterministic, likely some kind of race condition, and only appears to be happening if you are subscribed to new head notifications and attempt to fetch the block receipts on receipt of a notification.\r\n\r\nHere is some sample Javascript which can be used to force the issue to occur usually within a few blocks:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst Web3 = require('web3');\r\n\r\nconst web3 = new Web3(\"ws://...\");\r\n\r\nweb3.extend({\r\n    property: 'eth',\r\n    methods: [{\r\n        name: 'getBlockReceipts',\r\n        call: 'eth_getBlockReceipts',\r\n        params: 1,\r\n        inputFormatter: [web3.extend.formatters.inputDefaultBlockNumberFormatter],\r\n    }]\r\n})\r\n\r\nconst newHeads = web3.eth.subscribe('newBlockHeaders')\r\n\r\nnewHeads.on('data', async (header) => {\r\n\r\n    const { number, hash } = header\r\n    console.log(`New header, number = ${number}, hash = ${hash}`)\r\n\r\n    try {\r\n        const receipts = await web3.eth.getBlockReceipts(header.number)\r\n        console.log('Receipts', receipts.length)\r\n    } catch (err) {\r\n        const { message, stackTrace } = err\r\n        console.error(`Failed to get block receipts for number = ${number}, hash = ${hash}`, message, stackTrace)\r\n        process.exit(1)\r\n    }\r\n\r\n})\r\n```",
